missionEventData.data1: This is as close as we can get without alerting the rebels to our presence.
You'll need to use your Hyperdrives to travel the rest of the distance.
Acknowledged Repulse. Alpha Squadron prepare for final hyperspace jump.
I'm reading a YT-1300 powering up for Hyperspace.
Ignore it. They'll jump before we can do anything. Focus on taking out those Containers.
Detecting two DX-9 transports holding orbit about cargo zone.
Okay Alpha Squadron prepare to jump to the next location.
I'm reading a capital ship jumping into the system. Looks like a Mon Calamari Cruiser, Liberty Class.
Okay Alpha Squadron. Let's get this done before the Rebels can muster a response.
The Cruisers launching X-Wings. It's going to be difficult to jump with those fighters in close range. Engage them and hopefully we can make a gap for ourselves to jump out.
Another cruiser is exiting. She's launching E-Wings. It's going to be hard to get out of this one.
This is the Repulse. Land immediately before we're boxed in.
Okay, I'm sending the coordinates for the next jump. If we're lucky it will still be clear.
Okay Alpha02 and Alpha03 target those containers. I'll take out those transports.
Joining the attack on the cargo containers. Too bad the rebels know we're here.

While the Rebel leaders have denied all claims that they are planning to move against the legitimate imperial government now residing on Thyferra, our spies have shown a buildup of Rebel supply depots on the edge of Thyferran space. The director wants us to use the Phantom's cloaking ability to destroy these depots before help can arrive from the Rebel's mobile border force. Be careful, our Phantom's are invisible to radar, but as soon as we fire our cannons the Rebel's will know we are there.
Detecting a coded transmission from the shuttles. Looks like the rebels have been alerted to our presence.

missionEventData.data3: While we slowed down the buildup of armaments on our border, the Rebels responded far quicker than expected, and we were forced to make a jump into the heart of rebel space…
